records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison system for a total of fifteen (15) years.  That is ten (10) years initial confinement followed by five (5) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for ten (10) years.
The Court finds the defendant not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of probation:
1) Spend twelve (12) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing immediately;
2) Defendant is to speak to schools, three times per year, regarding participating in drug trade/trafficking, is the schools allow her to do so;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
6) Pay court costs;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
9) Defendant is to use one doctor for prescribing drugs and one pharmacist for filling prescriptions.  The defendant is to notify the agent of the doctor and all prescribed medications;
10) Pay restitution for the funeral expenses of the victim  TBD.  The Court will allow sixty days for the amount to be determined;
11) Maintain absolute sobriety.
Minutes.
